snippet.textDisplay: Those HiAce vans that you saw at the end of your drive seem to be getting very popular recently. I'm in the SF bay area and for the past 6 months I have been seeing those late 80's early 90's right hand drive japanese vans like the HiAce, Delica, HiJet, Urvan driving on the road about once every other week. Seems like most are turned into campers, and are often times the 4 wheel drive models that have better ground clearance than something like a Westfalia. I know in other parts of the world they're very common and parts are readily available, but I would imagine having to import items every time you need to fix something would be kind of a pain.
